{
    "title": "Browser Extension Security Audit",
    "breadcrumb": [
        {
            "title": "Others",
            "url": "/others"
        }
    ],
    "sections": [
        {
            "heading": "Architecture & Reconnaissance",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "Component Infrastructure",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "Extension Root",
                        "├── manifest.json (Global configuration)",
                        "├── background.js (Persistent service worker)",
                        "├── content_scripts/ (Web-injected logic)",
                        "├── popup/ (Interactive UI)",
                        "└── resources/ (Web-accessible assets)"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Asset Extraction & Discovery",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "# Locate local extensions (Chrome Windows)",
                        "%LOCALAPPDATA%\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\\Default\\Extensions\\",
                        "",
                        "# Download CRX directly from store",
                        "https://clients2.google.com/service/update2/crx?prodversion=100.0&x=id=EXTENSION_ID",
                        "",
                        "# Unpack extension for audit",
                        "unzip extension.crx -d extension_unpacked/"
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Static Analysis & Permissions",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "Critical manifest.json Flags",
                    "type": "list",
                    "content": [
                        "**<all_urls>**: Granting access to every website (High Risk).",
                        "**webRequestBlocking**: Ability to intercept and modify any network request.",
                        "**nativeMessaging**: Communication bridge with local system applications.",
                        "**content_security_policy**: Auditing for `unsafe-eval` or `unsafe-inline` weaknesses."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Vulnerability Hunting (Grep Patterns)",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "# Search for DOM XSS and eval injection",
                        "grep -rn \"eval(\\|innerHTML\\|document.write\" .",
                        "",
                        "# Search for script execution APIs",
                        "grep -rn \"chrome.scripting.executeScript\" .",
                        "",
                        "# Search for hardcoded API keys and secrets",
                        "grep -rn \"api_key\\|secret\\|token\" ."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Common Attack Vectors",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "Insecure Message Passing",
                    "type": "code_block",
                    "content": [
                        "// VULNERABLE: No sender validation in background script",
                        "chrome.runtime.onMessage.addListener((message, sender) => {",
                        "  if (message.action === 'execute') {",
                        "    eval(message.code); // Remote Code Execution (RCE)",
                        "  }",
                        "});"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "CORS & CSP Bypass Logic",
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "Extensions often act as a privileged proxy. If an extension exposes a `fetch` action via messaging without strict URL validation, a malicious webpage can leverage the extension to bypass CORS and access internal network services."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Exploitation & Dynamic Debugging",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "Dynamic Testing Environment",
                    "type": "list",
                    "content": [
                        "**Load Unpacked**: Enable Developer Mode in `chrome://extensions` to test modified source code.",
                        "**Message Injection**: Injecting payloads via `chrome.runtime.sendMessage` from the DevTools console.",
                        "**Burp Interception**: Configuring the browser to proxy extension traffic for API security analysis."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "heading": "Audit Toolkit",
                    "type": "list",
                    "content": [
                        "[CRXcavator](https://crxcavator.io/) - High-density automated security analysis platform.",
                        "[Tarnish](https://thehackerblog.com/tarnish/) - Deep static analyzer for Chrome extensions.",
                        "[Retire.js](https://retirejs.github.io/retire.js/) - Scanning for vulnerable third-party JavaScript libraries."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Comprehensive Audit Checklist",
            "subheadings": [
                {
                    "heading": "Verification Points",
                    "type": "list",
                    "content": [
                        "Review all `manifest.json` permissions for least-privilege compliance.",
                        "Audit cross-origin messaging for strict `sender.origin` validation.",
                        "Check for unencrypted sensitive data in `chrome.storage.local`.",
                        "Test web-accessible resources for potential privilege escalation or clickjacking.",
                        "Verify secure transmission (HTTPS) for all external API communications."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Reporting & Industry Standards",
            "type": "list",
            "content": [
                "[Google App Security Program](https://www.google.com/about/appsecurity/)",
                "[Mozilla Bug Bounty Program](https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/security/bug-bounty/)",
                "[XSS Prevention Guide](../enumeration/web/xss.md) - Contextual sanitization logic.",
                "[Code Review Methodology](code-review.md) - Advanced static analysis patterns."
            ]
        }
    ],
